01444                 int num_to_read =
01445                         yy_current_buffer->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
01446 
01447                 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
01448                         { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
01449 #ifdef YY_USES_REJECT
01450                         YY_FATAL_ERROR(
01451 "input buffer overflow, can't enlarge buffer because scanner uses REJECT" );
01452 #else
01453 
01454                         /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
01455                         YY_BUFFER_STATE b = yy_current_buffer;
01456 
01457                         int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
01458                                 (int) (yy_c_buf_p - b->yy_ch_buf);
01459 
01460                         if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
01461                                 {
01462                                 int new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
01463 
01464                                 if ( new_size <= 0 )
01465                                         b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
01466                                 else
01467                                         b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
01468 
01469                                 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
01470                                         /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
01471                                         yy_flex_realloc( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf,
01472                                                          b->yy_buf_size + 2 );
01473                                 }
01474                         else
01475                                 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
01476                                 b->yy_ch_buf = 0;
01477 
01478                         if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
01479                                 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
01480                                 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
01481 
01482                         yy_c_buf_p = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
01483 
01484                         num_to_read = yy_current_buffer->yy_buf_size -
01485                                                 number_to_move - 1;
01486 #endif
01487                         }
01488 
01489                 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
01490                         num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
01491 
01492                 /* Read in more data. */
01493                 YY_INPUT( (&yy_current_buffer->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
01494                         yy_n_chars, num_to_read );
01495 
01496                 yy_current_buffer->yy_n_chars = yy_n_chars;
01497                 }
01498 
01499         if ( yy_n_chars == 0 )
01500                 {
01501                 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
01502                         {
01503                         ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
01504                         yyrestart( yyin );
01505                         }
01506 
01507                 else
01508                         {
01509                         ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
01510                         yy_current_buffer->yy_buffer_status =
01511                                 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
01512                         }
01513                 }
01514 
01515         else
01516                 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
01517 
01518         yy_n_chars += number_to_move;
01519         yy_current_buffer->yy_ch_buf[yy_n_chars] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
01520         yy_current_buffer->yy_ch_buf[yy_n_chars + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
01521 
01522         yytext_ptr = &yy_current_buffer->yy_ch_buf[0];
01523 
01524         return ret_val;
01525         }

01633 
01634 #ifdef __cplusplus
01635 static int yyinput()
01636 #else
01637 static int input()
01638 #endif
01639         {
01640         int c;
01641 
01642         *yy_c_buf_p = yy_hold_char;
01643 
01644         if ( *yy_c_buf_p == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
01645                 {
01646                 /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
01647                  * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
01648                  * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
01649                  */
01650                 if ( yy_c_buf_p < &yy_current_buffer->yy_ch_buf[yy_n_chars] )
01651                         /* This was really a NUL. */
01652                         *yy_c_buf_p = '\0';
01653 
01654                 else
01655                         { /* need more input */
01656                         int offset = yy_c_buf_p - yytext_ptr;
01657                         ++yy_c_buf_p;
01658 
01659                         switch ( yy_get_next_buffer() )
01660                                 {
01661                                 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
01662                                         /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
01663                                          * sees that we've accumulated a
01664                                          * token and flags that we need to
01665                                          * try matching the token before
01666                                          * proceeding.  But for input(),
01667                                          * there's no matching to consider.
01668                                          * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
01669                                          * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
01670                                          */
01671 
01672                                         /* Reset buffer status. */
01673                                         yyrestart( yyin );
01674 
01675                                         /* fall through */
01676 
01677                                 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
01678                                         {
01679                                         if ( yywrap() )
01680                                                 return EOF;
01681 
01682                                         if ( ! yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof )
01683                                                 YY_NEW_FILE;
01684 #ifdef __cplusplus
01685                                         return yyinput();
01686 #else
01687                                         return input();
01688 #endif
01689                                         }
01690 
01691                                 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
01692                                         yy_c_buf_p = yytext_ptr + offset;
01693                                         break;
01694                                 }
01695                         }
01696                 }
01697 
01698         c = *(unsigned char *) yy_c_buf_p;      /* cast for 8-bit char's */
01699         *yy_c_buf_p = '\0';     /* preserve yytext */
01700         yy_hold_char = *++yy_c_buf_p;
01701 
01702         if ( c == '\n' )
01703                 ++yylineno;
01704 
01705         return c;
01706         }

01726 #else
01727 void yy_switch_to_buffer( new_buffer )
01728 YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer;
01729 #endif
01730         {

01750         yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
